{{> header}}
<div class="about-body">
  <div class="about-body-width">
    <h1 class="mt-5">ABOUT MUSIC-CONTACT</h1>
    <p class="mt-3 d-flex justify-content-center text-center" style="font-size: 1.3em;">Welcome to our contact page! If you have any questions,
      feedback, or inquiries, please don't hesitate to get in touch with us. You can reach us via email or through our
      social media channels.<br/><br/>

      Email:
      You can contact us via email at music-contact@gmail.com. We will do our best to respond to your message as soon
      as possible.<br/><br/>

      Social Media:
      You can also connect with us on social media. You can find us on Twitter, Facebook, and Instagram. 
      Feel free to send us a message or a direct message, and we'll get back to you as soon as we
      can.<br/><br/>

      Thank you for visiting our contact page, and we look forward to hearing from you soon!</p>
    <h1 class="mt-5">CONTACT WITH US</h1>
    <p class="mt-1 mb-1">Contact with us if you have any issue!</p>
    <div class="filter-container">
      <form action="" method="post">
        <div class="mb-3">
          <label for="name" class="form-label">Name</label>
          <input name="name" type="text" class="form-control" id="email">
        </div>
        <div class="mb-3">
          <label for="email" class="form-label">Email address</label>
          <input name="email" type="email" class="form-control" id="email">
        </div>
        <div class="mb-3">
          <label for="message" class="mb-1">Message</label>
          <textarea name="message" class="form-control" id="message"></textarea>
        </div>
        <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary-see-detail">Submit</button>
      </form>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<script>
  window.addEventListener("load", (event) => {
    const headerHeight = getComputedStyle(document.querySelector('.sticky-top')).height
    document.querySelector('body').style.height = `calc(100vh - ${headerHeight})`
  });
</script>